column16: encodes a arginine decarboxylase (ADC)%2C a rate-limiting enzyme that catalyzes the first step of polyamine (PA) biosynthesis via ADC pathway in Arabidopsis thaliana. Arabidopsis genome has two ADC paralogs%2C ADC1 and ADC2. ADC2 is stress-inducible (osmotic stress). Double mutant analysis showed that ADC genes are essential for the production of PA%2C and are required for normal seed development. Overexpression causes phenotypes similar to GA-deficient plants and these plants show reduced levels of GA due to lower expression levels of AtGA20ox1%2C AtGA3ox3 and AtGA3ox1.

ID=AT4G36380;Name=AT4G36380;Note=Cytochrome P450 superfamily protein;curator_summary=Encodes a cytochrome P-450 gene that is involved in leaf blade expansion by controlling polar cell expansion in the leaf length direction. Member of the CYP90C CYP450 family. ROT3 was shown to be involved in brassinosteroid biosynthesis%2C most likely in the conversion step of typhasterol (TY) to castasterone (CS). As 6-deoxo-CS was unable to restore the phenotype of rot3-1%2C it has been postulated that ROT3 might be specifically involved in the conversion of TY to CS in the C6-oxidation pathway of brassinolide. Recently%2C CYP90C1 was shown to catalyse the C-23 hydroxylation of several brassinosteroids (the enzyme has a broad specificity for 22-hydroxylated substrates).;symbol=ROT3;full_name=ROTUNDIFOLIA 3;computational_description=ROTUNDIFOLIA 3 (ROT3)%3B CONTAINS InterPro DOMAIN/s: Cytochrome P450 (InterPro:IPR001128)%2C Cytochrome P450%2C E-class%2C group IV (InterPro:IPR002403)%2C Cytochrome P450%2C conserved site (InterPro:IPR017972)%3B BEST Arabidopsis thaliana protein match is: cytochrome P450%2C family 90%2C subfamily D%2C polypeptide 1 (TAIR:AT3G13730.1)%3B Has 30201 Blast hits to 17322 proteins in 780 species: Archae - 12%3B Bacteria - 1396%3B Metazoa - 17338%3B Fungi - 3422%3B Plants - 5037%3B Viruses - 0%3B Other Eukaryotes - 2996 (source: NCBI BLink).;Dbxref=PMID:10430960,PMID:9694802,PMID:8625845,PMID:11978864,PMID:12226529,PMID:12407202,PMID:15703058,PMID:15908602,PMID:17038516,PMID:17138693,PMID:18650403,PMID:19200151,PMID:20538889,PMID:23264517,locus:2115220;locus_type=protein_coding
column16: Encodes a cytochrome P-450 gene that is involved in leaf blade expansion by controlling polar cell expansion in the leaf length direction. Member of the CYP90C CYP450 family. ROT3 was shown to be involved in brassinosteroid biosynthesis%2C most likely in the conversion step of typhasterol (TY) to castasterone (CS). As 6-deoxo-CS was unable to restore the phenotype of rot3-1%2C it has been postulated that ROT3 might be specifically involved in the conversion of TY to CS in the C6-oxidation pathway of brassinolide. Recently%2C CYP90C1 was shown to catalyse the C-23 hydroxylation of several brassinosteroids (the enzyme has a broad specificity for 22-hydroxylated substrates).
